ignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":0,"created_at":"2021-09-24T20:00:11Z","updated_at":"2022-10-24T15:21:32Z","closed_at":null,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"Update: done for forecasting in #1436, still needs to be done for classifiers.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nTags of a foreceaster may carry extra information regarding restrictions of inputs to class methods, such as `scitype:y` which tells the user whether univariate or multivariate input is allowed.\r\nCurrently, this is not captured in the docstrings of user facing class methods.\r\n\r\nThese tag based information should be explicit in class docstrings, e.g., telling the user which restrictions apply, depending on tag values. E.g., if `\"scitype:y\"=\"univariate\"`, then `X` must be univariate, etc.\r\n\r\nWe should do this both in forecasting and classification for the tags that affect the input format specification and/or the output.","closed_by":null,"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sktime/sktime/issues/1451/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sktime/sktime/issues/1451/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}